entry.content: Trichocolletes venustus is hundreds of km outside its previously known range.

entry.content: Awful photo!

entry.content: Beetle is possibly Castiarina sp. (thanks SJ)?

entry.title: Dillwynia cinerascens s.s.
entry.content: A very large, grey form.

entry.title: Geranium sp. 3
entry.content: 1st pic shows blue-purple dehiscence lines on anthers. 2nd pic show broad lobed over-winter leaf (bottom - seems to have spreading hairs) & thin-dissected summer leaves (top left). Peduncle seems to have appressed hairs.

entry.title: Medicago polymorpha
entry.content: Distinctive laciniate stipule at base of petiole shown well in third pic. Quite similar to Trifolium dubium otherwise.

entry.title: Acaena echinata
entry.content: ID feature of echinata is glabrous leaves except for hairy main vein(s) on lower surface. Then fruit spines are all approximatelythe same length and stems are glabrous-sparsely hairy.

entry.title: Brassica fruticulosa, Pieris rapae rapae
entry.content: Coincidentally feeding on what is possibly its host plant at this location.

entry.title: Lepidoptera spp.
entry.content: I think this is on a weedy grass leaf.

entry.title: Carex divisa
entry.content: In inundated areas.

entry.title: Convolvulus angustissimus subsp. omnigracilis
entry.content: ID features of this subspecies are in 3rd pic (small lobes on basal leaves) and 1st & 2nd pic (dissected and linear lobes on mid-stem leaves).

entry.title: Cicendia quadrangularis
entry.content: Tiny plants.
